comments: Thompson (GSW) slightly extends his arm into Forbes (DEN) as he disengages into his shooting motion.
Thompson (GSW) briefly has an arm around Jokic (DEN) during the screen and immediately slides it off.
Thompson (GSW) makes marginal contact with Forbes (DEN) that does not affect his shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) places two hands on Looney (GSW) and drives him off of his spot as he goes to set the pick.
As Looney (GSW) is retracting his arm, Jokic (DEN) raises his own arm into it to draw attention to the contact.  The contact does not affect Jokic's SQBR.
The Nuggets signal for, and are awarded a timeout before Green (DEN) starts his dribble.  Therefore, they are allowed to advance the ball to midcourt following the timeout.
Looney (GSW) maintains a legal guarding position defending Jokic (DEN) in the post and during his shot attempt.
Morris (DEN) grabs the long rebound and any contact with Wiggins (GSW) is considered incidental.
Rivers (DEN) and Thompson (GSW) make marginal leg to leg contact with each other.
Morris (DEN) reaches in and makes contact to Curry's (GSW) arm that affects his shot attempt just as he gathers the ball and enters his upward shooting motion.

Jokic (DEN) raises his arm upwards into Looney's (GSW) slightly extended arm, but the contact does not affect his ability to defend the play.  Additionally, the contact by Looney does not affect Jokic's SQBR.
Curry (GSW) makes incidental contact with Morris's (DEN) arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
